Functions in this full FT + prototype version:

Component	Role
PrototypeBank	K=8 learnable prototype vectors P ∈ ℝ^{K×D} — the "slots"
PrototypeCrossAttention	z_k = g_φ(p_k, O) — each prototype attends to visual context O independently
PrototypeWarmupCallback	Steps 0–499: freeze LLM, train prototypes only. Step 500+: unfreeze LLM
TimeEstimationCallback	Prints ETA + GPU memory at each log step
Full FT (no LoRA)	Entire LLM backbone is plastic (freeze_llm=False, lora_enable=False)
Frozen vision tower + merger	freeze_vision_tower=True, freeze_merger=True — visual encoder is fixed
Diversity loss	loss_diversity_lambda=0.05 — pushes prototypes apart
Focus loss	loss_focus_lambda=0.01 — encourages sparse attention weights
Data packing	Sequences packed up to 8192 tokens, max 2 instances per batch
DeepSpeed ZeRO-3 + CPU offload	Fits 3B full FT across 4 GPUs via zero3_offload.json
Learning rates:

LLM: 1e-5 (low — catastrophic forgetting risk with full FT)
Prototype modules: 5e-4 (high — randomly initialised, needs fast convergence)
The key design property: ∂z_k/∂z_j = 0 — all K prototypes are computed in parallel with no cross-slot gradient, so each slot learns independently. 



Loss Functions in Prototype Mode
What's computed (3 losses)
1. L_CE — Cross-Entropy (monkey_patch_forward_lvr.py:313-316)


Standard next-token prediction loss.
[proto_k] token positions are masked from labels (IGNORE_INDEX)
so prototype slots don't "teach" the model to predict them as text.
2. L_div — Diversity (monkey_patch_forward_lvr.py:327-332)


Z_norm = F.normalize(Z_f, dim=-1)           # [B, K, D]
sim    = bmm(Z_norm, Z_norm.T)               # [B, K, K]
loss_div = (sim[:, off_diag] ** 2).mean()   # penalise cos² between pairs
Goal: push prototype output vectors apart so each slot specialises in a different visual aspect.
λ = 0.05

3. L_focus — Attention Entropy (monkey_patch_forward_lvr.py:334-337)


entropy    = -(A * (A + eps).log()).sum(dim=-1)  # [B, K]
loss_focus = entropy.mean()
Goal: minimising entropy → peaked/focused attention per slot → each prototype attends to specific regions, not the whole image.
λ = 0.01

How they combine (trainer compute_loss)

L_proto = 0.05 × L_div + 0.01 × L_focus
L_total = L_CE  +  1.0 × L_proto
loss_lvr_lambda = 1.0 is set in the shell script. The prototype aux loss is passed through the loss_lvr field in the output dataclass (reusing that slot).

Where each is configured
Parameter	Set in	Value
loss_diversity_lambda	params.py:92, shell script	0.05
loss_focus_lambda	params.py:93, shell script	0.01
loss_lvr_lambda (scales L_proto)	params.py:34, shell script	1.0
loss_lvr_fct (unused in proto mode)	shell script	mse
